claim.claim-text:
1. A method for performing and scheduling actions related to viewing and recording programs, comprising:
generating a display of a plurality of program listings;
selecting a program from the plurality of program listings;
generating a display of an action pop-up menu overlaid over the plurality of program listings in response to a first user selection on an input device, wherein the action pop-up menu comprises a listing of a plurality of selectable scheduling actions related to the selected program, the listing including at least one action unrelated to recording;
selecting one of the plurality of scheduling actions using a highlight region; and
scheduling the selected action in response to a second user selection on the input device, wherein the first and second user selections are made by selecting the same key on the input device.

12. A system for performing and scheduling actions related to viewing and recording programs, the system comprising a processing system, the processing system configured to:
generate a display of a plurality of program listings;
receive a user selection of a program from the plurality of program listings;
generate a display of an action pop-up menu overlaid over the plurality of program listings in response to a first user selection on an input device, wherein the action pop-up menu comprises a listing of a plurality of selectable scheduling actions related to the selected program, the listing including at least one action unrelated to recording;
receive a user selection of one of the plurality of scheduling actions using a highlight region; and
schedule the selected action in response to a second user selection on the input device, wherein the first and second user selections are made by selecting the same key on the input device.

23. A method for performing and scheduling actions related to viewing and recording programs, comprising:
generating a display of a plurality of program listings;
receiving a first user selection of a program from the plurality of program listings;
generating a display of an action pop-up menu overlaid over the plurality of program listings in response to the first user selection received from an input interface, wherein the action pop-up menu comprises a listing of a plurality of selectable scheduling actions related to the selected program, the listing including at least one action unrelated to recording;
receiving a second user selection of one of the plurality of scheduling actions; and
scheduling the selected action in response to the second user selection received from the input interface, wherein the first and second user selections are made by selecting a same area of the input interface.

29. A system for performing and scheduling actions related to viewing and recording programs, the system comprising a processing system, the processing system configured to:
generate a display of a plurality of program listings;
receive a first user selection of a program from the plurality of program listings;
generate a display of an action pop-up menu overlaid over the plurality of program listings in response to the first user selection received from an input interface, wherein the action pop-up menu comprises a listing of a plurality of selectable scheduling actions related to the selected program, the listing including at least one action unrelated to recording;
receive a second user selection of one of the plurality of scheduling actions; and
schedule the selected action in response to the second user selection received from the input interface, wherein the first and second user selections are made by selecting a same area of the input interface.

35. A method for performing and scheduling actions related to viewing and recording programs, comprising:
generating a display of a plurality of program listings;
receiving a first user selection of a program from the plurality of program listings;
generating a display of an action pop-up menu overlaid over the plurality of program listings in response to the first user selection received from an input interface, wherein the action pop-up menu comprises a listing of a plurality of selectable scheduling actions related to the selected program, the listing including at least one action unrelated to recording;
receiving a second user selection of one of the plurality of scheduling actions; and
scheduling the selected action in response to the second user selection received from the input interface, wherein the first and second user selections are made by selecting a same component of the input interface.

36. A system for performing and scheduling actions related to viewing and recording programs, the system comprising a processing system, the processing system configured to:
generate a display of a plurality of program listings;
receive a first user selection of a program from the plurality of program listings;
generate a display of an action pop-up menu overlaid over the plurality of program listings in response to the first user selection received from an input interface, wherein the action pop-up menu comprises a listing of a plurality of selectable scheduling actions related to the selected program, the listing including at least one action unrelated to recording;
receive a second user selection of one of the plurality of scheduling actions; and
schedule the selected action in response to the second user selection received from the input interface, wherein the first and second user selections are made by selecting a same component of the input interface.
